<img width="1534" height="1438" class="wp-image-1392754" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kano-state-map-e1646198175960.jpg" alt="Kano rice millers" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kano-state-map-e1646198175960.jpg?width=1534&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1534w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kano-state-map-e1646198175960-300x281.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kano-state-map-e1646198175960-1024x960.jpg?width=1024&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1024w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kano-state-map-e1646198175960-768x720.jpg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kano-state-map-e1646198175960-1200x1125.jpg?width=1200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1534px) 100vw, 1534px" /> By Bashir Bello About 201 Kano residents have been hospitalized after inhaling expired chemical from a cylinder at a  scrap metal collection point in  Sharada Industrial area of the state. It was gathered that the incident happened when a scrap collector dismantled the cylinder and the expired chemical escaped into the air resulting in many residents, after inhaling the toxic substance, went down unconscious, coughing and vomiting. Meanwhile, Kano State Police Command, yesterday, said it had cordon off the scrap metal collection point where the chemical emission emanated. Confirming the incident, the state police spokesperson, SP Abdullahi Haruna, said the incident happened on Friday evening and he was yet to get details. Haruna said, “We are yet to get details of the incident. “We have cordoned off the area. And we have deployed experts to the area who have already swung into action.” On his part, spokesperson for Kano State Fire Service, Saminu Yusuf, said his agency had brought the situation in the area under control. “We have succeeded in bringing the situation under control. We got some experts from a private firm with technical know-how about the situation who brought some chemical to control the emission. The chemical was mixed with water from our water tank to neutralize the expired chemical spread”, Yusuf said. “Several persons were evacuated to hospital. While we were evacuating the victims, other good samaritans were also lending helping hand.” Earlier, officials of the  National Emergency Management Agency, NEMA, in Kano put the number of victims at 201. The agency said the victims were rushed to Murtala Muhammad Specialist Hospital, Sharada Industrial Hospital and Ja’en Hospital for medical attention.   Kano map By Bashir Bello KANO --- Not fewer than 201 Kano residents have been hospitalized after inhaling an expired chemical from a cylinder at a scrap metal collection point in the Sharada Industrial area of the state. It was gathered that the incident happened when a scrap man dismantled… In "News" Two hundred and one residents of Sharada Quarters, Kano, were on Friday reportedly hospitalised after inhaling chemicals from a cylinder dismantled by metal scrappers. In "News" Furniture shop owner, Abdulkareem Adam Balogun By Bashir Bello KANO --- A furniture shop owner, Abulkareem Adam Balogun in building that collapsed as a result of explosion in Aba road in Sabon Gari, Fagge Local Government area of Kano State has narrated how he narrowly escaped death after the explosion that went… In "News"